ire - I'm talking about We Three Kings, Silent Night, The First Noel during music classes which include children of all faiths, readings of the Nativity in Grade 2 reading lessons which include children of all faiths, Lenten observances (Pancake Day and forehead ashen crosses to include children of all faiths), Easter eggs (not &quot;spring spheres&quot; as one school now calls them). &#10;Right?&#10;p.s. religious expression is not the issue here. Using public schools for that end is. What on earth anything an American president had to say has anything to do with our Constitution remains unclear. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="870" language="en" documentId="1361" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="canajunlady" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/tempers-flare-over-prayer-in-schools-1.1104775" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1361" notes="" title="Tempers flare over prayer in schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="156"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="157" end="661"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="662" end="668"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="669" end="870"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51"/></xmi:XMI>